  "response": "There are several institutes and centers in and around Noida that provide support and education for differently abled children. Here are a few notable options:\n\n1. Tamana Autism Centre\n- Located in Noida\n- Specializes in autism support and education\n- Provides therapies and skill development programs\n\n2. Action For Ability Development and Inclusion (AADI)\n- Located in Noida\n- Supports children with multiple disabilities\n- Offers special education and rehabilitation services\n\n3. Indian Institute of Cerebral Palsy (IICP)\n- Located in Noida\n- Focuses on children with cerebral palsy\n- Provides therapy and educational support\n\n4. National Institute for Empowerment of Persons with Visual Disabilities (NIEPVD)\n- Located in Dehradun (near Noida)\n- Supports visually impaired children\n- Offers educational and skill development programs\n\n5. Desire Society\n- Located in Noida\n- Works with differently abled children\n- Provides inclusive education and support\n\n6. Vatsal Special School\n- Located in Noida\n- Offers special education for children with different disabilities\n\nI recommend contacting these centers directly for more specific information about their programs, admission process, and suitability for a specific child's needs.",
